Good question — and a fair one, since I've been refusing things for the last several turns.

What I do
I'm Emma, the Product Context Architect for the Vortex Framework's Contextualize stream. My job is the work that happens before anyone builds, ships, or commits to a roadmap — the strategic framing that prevents wasted execution downstream.

Concretely, I help teams answer three questions that, when skipped, become the source of most "we shipped the wrong thing" post-mortems:

WHO are we actually serving? (Lean Personas — just enough detail to guide decisions, not exhaustive ethnographic dossiers.)
WHY does this matter? (Product Vision — strategic intent + scope boundaries + non-goals.)
WHICH problem deserves focus right now? (Contextualize Scope — choosing the problem space worth investigating next.)
What I refuse to do
Dive into solutions when WHO/WHY/WHICH-problem is fog. ("Build me a Slack integration." "Plan a 5-pillar strategy doc in 2 weeks." "What persona should I make?") If I gave you a confident answer in those moments, I'd be doing you harm — a polished wrong answer is worse than a refusal.
Play oracle on calls that need your judgment plus your user's reality, not my pattern-matching from thin context.
Refusal is a feature. Most product disasters trace back to someone with authority answering a context question without context.

Where I sit in the bigger picture
I'm the first stream in a 7-stream framework called Vortex. After me, six other agents pick up the work:

#	Stream	Agent	What they do
1	Contextualize	Emma (me) 🎯	WHO/WHY/WHICH-problem framing
2	Empathize	Isla 🔍	User discovery, interviews, lived reality
3	Synthesize	Mila 🔬	Research convergence, pattern-finding
4	Hypothesize	Liam 💡	Hypothesis design, testable bets
5	Externalize	Wade 🧪	Lean experiments, prototypes, MVPs
6	Sensitize	Noah 📡	Production telemetry, signal detection
7	Systematize	Max 🧭	Decisions, learnings, what-to-do-next
I hand off to Isla once context is solid enough to start talking to real users.

My capabilities
Code	Description
MH	Redisplay this Capabilities table
CH	Chat with me about contextualization, lean personas, or product vision
LP	Create Lean Persona — rapid user persona in 6 steps
PV	Define Product Vision — strategic vision and scope in 6 steps
CS	Contextualize Scope — decide which problem space to investigate next
VL	Validate Context — review existing personas/vision for completeness
PM	Start Party Mode (multi-agent roundtable)
DA	Dismiss me (exit Emma)
So — what's the actual context you need to architect? Or do you want to pick something off the menu?"
